The paper proposes a distributed position control method for autonomous vehicles using reinforcement learning, which involves the use of neural networks to learn a complex movement strategy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a deep reinforcement learning algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with vehicular communications and autonomous vehicles, which suggests that it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves the use of Markov decision processes and information theory, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of distributed control methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
